[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating SecurityException in methods**\n\nI’m considering if there’s another way for `Class.getDeclaredMethods` to throw a `SecurityException` in native environments. I'm wondering if the absence of native image reflection metadata could cause issues. It seems like if you call `getDeclaredMethods` on a class without that metadata, it might just return empty instead of throwing a `SecurityException`. I’ll need to explore this further to understand the behavior in native contexts.\n\n**Evaluating coverage tool functionality**\n\nI'm analyzing how the coverage tool tracks dynamic-access call sites. It intercepts calls and doesn’t require passing them directly. If I can get to line 338 and it fails later, then I think it’s covered. But can the test be allowed to fail? Hmm, I wonder. Maybe line 338 can still be reached if Class.getDeclaredMethods throws a SecurityException due to Native Image being unsupported, but I’m not sure about that either.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_08ef2872fae49a900169fa6509aa84819fa7ae612421c53441\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-mUn7QkcSxv80wxZrLB6lzzYeU2aZtBAP7k4S7GhuUkTBKs1rsHx-UAe_r0J4ZD9oC2Jxxs1RusVRLDNiSPO3IHP49whFpXAEhrpJR16eRyPrvBEzqqOz7yJMHgNYitd0jyxNH5kb5x-qO7sxDBz5Ny7dajd4EWFjbKaBIkYdKRQLAzamKbp1vnybT8xEXqdf0gPElg40sO84g3IUDQF27n7b3VPKkG-9NRQw3kgtJZDzdZZ2ZC7IWwaaaZsiScYw2U1EcTzXcd4vH77UmmQTylOcbusDacPNnKE4-S3yXzzXN017WVED-ViZ-_VHm4GKh3foogRG3Qh-dPe93tqerelyBWnif7aBE3WCwe4kKQoTMVHZAvikJOw0us3c_BWNMq46XsXlUxIhBZVgdOcRNBaSAUKqonlyVPKQpCT8WJ1lUGoXGBx_Q1nTnXSjSNPTTRcHqyGqtPBGYY2szUwvPKhnAwLFz1jcV9NM2x479rzEF3XLVSa4IrlANIertZ7-WD1xSjASsMqaqbQIvQx1J74iO93JmQ3n8zBJhJCz211OeHK-yrY5KQ80z2mVRbzx1isBFAdTaTsiwuY6wq5HgMwUbxcF0tFrnjRpQPLOzVdYUp-K__53lpJuIgpHHYX-YofO8xbpdnk2ClFhZwjnZKPlmIejDl-xGS5tEoX50AIWk3uwMWHX2PZU5VhfelVLpNh5AaOhiKwmxeYzDBLCejb9tn79qo5IeUs0239SPJHb-dOX24viAArii8eIOIxkkd7s2m4X-5Qa2fbHHd