ublicFallbackMethodHolder` through an isolated byte-array `ClassLoader`.\n- With `SecurityManager` denying `accessDeclaredMembers`, `Class#getDeclaredMethods()` should throw `SecurityException` for that separately loaded class.\n- That forces `JavaMembers` into the catch block that calls `clazz.getMethods()` at line 338.\n- The dynamic class-loading path catches `Error` and validates it with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)` for Native Image compatibility.\n\nKept:\n\n- The existing `build.gradle` JVM arg for allowing `SecurityManager` on JDKs where it is still supported.\n\nI did not run tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_08ef2872fae49a900169fa658a77d8819fbf9d20aeac06e4b5\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1103, "output": 693, "cacheRead": 84992, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 86788, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778017661569, "responseId": "resp_08ef2872fae49a900169fa657e64b4819fa0d0b761a0d4a2b5"}, "toolResults": []}
